\cf0 The Role of Pipelines in Petroleum Supply\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardeftab720\fi720\sl480\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \ulnone In discussing pipeline safety legislation, it is useful to remind the Committee of the role oil pipelines play in energy supply.  An understanding of this role leads to appreciation of the need for effective and workable policies that provide certainty so this key part of the petroleum distribution system operates efficiently and safely. \
About 40 percent of the total U.S. energy supply comes from petroleum, but the transportation sector depends on petroleum for 97 percent of its energy.  Two-thirds of domestic crude oil and refined products transportation is provided by pipeline.  Pipelines do this safely and efficiently.  The cost to deliver a gallon of petroleum by pipeline is very low, typically 2-3 cents per gallon.  Transportation \'96 airlines, automobiles, trucks, barges and ships -- could not function without pipelines to deliver crude oil to refineries and refinery output of petroleum fuels to consumers in various parts of the country.  The national oil pipeline system is a bargain for consumers and an absolutely essential part of the US economy.\
